<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,229,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,427,383,409]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Characteristics:—</emphasis>
Deb (2020) synonymised 
<taxonomicName authority="J.D.Hooker, 1873" authorityName="Davis &amp; Mvungi" authorityYear="2004" box="[736,891,384,409]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psilanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bridsoniae">
<emphasis box="[736,891,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">P. bridsoniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wall. ex Wight &amp; Arn.)" authorityName="J.-F.Leroy" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Wall. ex Wight &amp; Arn." box="[976,1435,384,410]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psilanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wightianus">
<emphasis box="[976,1134,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">P. wightianus</emphasis>
(Wall. ex Wight &amp; Arn.)
</taxonomicName>
J.-F.Leroy and, in error, under 
<taxonomicName authority="J.D.Hooker, 1873" authorityName="J.D.Hooker" authorityYear="1873" box="[516,647,423,448]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psilanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fragrans">
<emphasis box="[516,647,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">P. fragrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I have no hesitation in resurrecting 
<taxonomicName authority="J.D.Hooker, 1873" authorityName="Davis &amp; Mvungi" authorityYear="2004" box="[1085,1241,423,448]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psilanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bridsoniae">
<emphasis box="[1085,1241,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">P. bridsoniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and providing a new name in 
<taxonomicName box="[312,391,461,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Coffea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[312,391,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Coffea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[406,663,461,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Coffea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="neobridsoniae">
<emphasis box="[406,663,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Coffea neobridsoniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very easily set apart from and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wall. ex Wight &amp; Arn." authorityName="Wight &amp; Arn." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Coffea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wightiana">
<emphasis box="[1063,1216,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">C. wightiana</emphasis>
Wall. ex Wight &amp; Arn.
</taxonomicName>
, and in particular by its rather open habit (vs. congested, spiny-looking), membranous leaves (vs. chartaceous) with 4 or 5 secondary veins (vs. 3 or 4), long-acuminate leaf apex (vs. acute), and presence of colleters at the base of the hypanthium (vs. absent).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,229,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,266,615,641]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Note:</emphasis>
—A new name is required for this species because there is already a 
<taxonomicName box="[1090,1261,616,642]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Coffea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1090,1168,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Coffea</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with the same specific epithet: 
<taxonomicName authority="Davis &amp; Mvungi (2004)" authorityName="Davis &amp; Mvungi" authorityYear="2004" box="[344,799,654,680]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psilanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bridsoniae">
<emphasis box="[344,504,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">C. bridsoniae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Davis, A. P. &amp; Mvungi, E. F." box="[511,799,654,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" pagination="237 - 245" refId="ref2549" refString="Davis, A. P. &amp; Mvungi, E. F. (2004) Two new and endangered species of Coffea (Rubiaceae) from the Eastern Arc Mountains (Tanzania) and notes on associated conservation issues. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 146: 237 - 245." type="journal article" year="2004">Davis &amp; Mvungi (2004)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
